# function for removing URLs, i.e.,
#  "http" followed by any non-space letters
removeURL <- function(x) gsub("http[^[:space:]]*", "", x)
# function for removing anything other than English letters or space
removeNumPunct <- function(x) gsub("[^[:alpha:][:space:]]*", "", x)
# customize stop words
myStopwords <- c(setdiff(stopwords('english'), c("r", "big")),
                 "use", "see", "used", "via", "amp", "fuck")
corpus.raw <- tweets.df$text %>% VectorSource() %>% Corpus()
# text cleaning
# build a corpus and specify the source to be character vectors
corpus.cleaned <- corpus.raw %>%
  # remove numbers and punctuations
  tm_map(content_transformer(removeNumPunct)) %>%
  # convert to lower case
  tm_map(content_transformer(tolower)) %>%
  # remove URLs
  tm_map(content_transformer(removeURL)) %>%
  # remove stopwords
  tm_map(removeWords, myStopwords) %>%
  # remove extra whitespace
  tm_map(stripWhitespace)
## stem words
corpus.stemmed <- corpus.cleaned %>% tm_map(stemDocument)
## stem completion
stemCompletion2 <- function(x, dictionary)
{
  x <- unlist(strsplit(as.character(x), " "))
  x <- x[x != ""]
  x <- stemCompletion(x, dictionary=dictionary)
  x <- paste(x, sep="", collapse=" ")
  stripWhitespace(x)
}
corpus.completed <- corpus.stemmed %>%
  lapply(stemCompletion2, dictionary=corpus.cleaned) %>%
  VectorSource() %>% Corpus()
# original text
corpus.raw[[1]]$content %>% strwrap(60) %>% writeLines()

# remove sparse terms
m2 <- tdm %>% removeSparseTerms(sparse = 0.95) %>% as.matrix()
# calculate distance matrix
dist.matrix <- m2 %>% scale() %>% dist()
# hierarchical clustering
fit <- dist.matrix %>% hclust(method = "ward.D")
plot(fit)

fit %>% rect.hclust(k = 6)

# cut tree into 6 clusters
groups <- fit %>% cutree(k = 6)
m3 <- m2 %>% t()
# transpose the matrix to cluster documents (tweets)
set.seed(122)
# set a fixed random seed to make the result reproducible
k <- 3
# number of clusters
kmeansResult <- kmeans(m3, k)
round(kmeansResult$centers, digits = 3)
##   great people  vote  will thank   now presidency today senate obama
## 1 0.073   0.00 0.063 0.067 0.055 0.000      0.082 0.087  0.062 0.072
## 2 0.106   0.03 0.091 0.076 0.030 1.015      0.091 0.015  0.091 0.045
## 3 0.106   1.03 0.091 0.106 0.091 0.000      0.015 0.061  0.045 0.000
# cluster centers

for (i in 1:k){
  cat(paste("cluster ", i, ":  ", sep = ""))
  s <- sort(kmeansResult$centers[i, ], decreasing = T)
  cat(names(s)[1:5], "\n")
  # print the tweets of every cluster
  #print(tweets[which(kmeansResult$cluster==i)])
}
## cluster 1:  today presidency great obama will 
## cluster 2:  now great vote presidency senate 
## cluster 3:  people great will vote thank
dtm <- tdm %>% as.DocumentTermMatrix()
dtm <- dtm %>% removeSparseTerms(sparse = 0.95)

ui = unique(dtm$i)
dtm.new = dtm[ui,]
library(topicmodels)
## Warning: package 'topicmodels' was built under R version 3.4.4
lda <- LDA(dtm.new, k = 3)
# find 8 topics
term <- terms(lda, 7)
# first 7 terms of every topic
term <- apply(term, MARGIN = 2, paste, collapse = ", ") %>% print
##                                                Topic 1 
##  "today, now, will, people, presidency, senate, thank" 
##                                                Topic 2 
## "obama, great, presidency, people, will, thank, today" 
##                                                Topic 3 
## "vote, today, senate, great, presidency, obama, thank"
rdm.topics <- topics(lda)
library(data.table)
## Warning: package 'data.table' was built under R version 3.4.3
# 1st topic identified for every document (tweet)
rdm.topics <- data.frame(date=as.IDate(tweets.df$created[ui]),
                         topic=rdm.topics)

sentiments <- sentiment(tweets.df$text)
table(sentiments$polarity)
## 
## negative  neutral positive 
##       48      956      140
sentiments$score <- 0
sentiments$score[sentiments$polarity == "positive"] <- 1
sentiments$score[sentiments$polarity == "negative"] <- -1
sentiments$date <- as.IDate(tweets.df$created)
result <- aggregate(score ~ date, data = sentiments, sum)
plot(result, type = "l")
